cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of downlink channel state information (CSI) feedback in a frequency division duplex (FDD) massive MIMO system. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the transmission, processing, and utilization of information. The paper also involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for compression and reconstruction of CSI, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper proposes an analog feedback scheme that simplifies the operation and provides a low-latency alternative, which could fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with the use of massive MIMO systems, which could also fall under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
